article.description: Tyler Hall scored five of his 16 points in overtime to help Montana State rally to a 73-72 win over Northern Arizona on Saturday, ending a three-game skid.
article.headline: Montana State downs Northern Arizona 74-72 in OT
article.linkText: Montana State downs Northern Arizona 74-72 in OT
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Tyler Hall scored five of his 16 points in overtime to help Montana State rally to a 73-72 win over Northern Arizona on Saturday, ending a three-game skid. Hall tied it at 60 with a 3-pointer to force the overtime, then put the Bobcats up 67-64 with a jumper with 1:17 left in OT. Hall's 3 with 48 seconds to go gave Montana State a 72-68 lead, and his free throw put the Bobcats up 73-69. NAU's Felix Rivera-Vega hit a 3 to pull within 73-72 with 10 seconds left. MSU's Sarp Gobeloglu made a one of two free throws to make it 74-72 before NAU's Torry Johnson missed a 3 at the buzzer. Marcus Colbert scored 23 points and Zach Green had 10 with 12 rebounds for the Bobcats (6-8, 1-1 Big Sky Conference). Kris Yanku scored 19, Rivera-Vega added 15 and Marcus DeBerry and Mike Green each had 13 for NAU (2-11, 0-2).
